shared_text:
Roane State Community College
May 18 at 10:19 PM ·

🎓 CONGRATS, CLASS OF 2020! 🎓 Roane State’s drive-through graduate recognition events produced “absolute joy in the form of laughter, smiles and tears of happiness."

The events were held at eight Roane State campuses last week as a way of congratulating the graduates while campuses remain closed due to COVID-19. Students and their families received Class of 2020 yard signs noting their achievement, along with college memorabilia.

Roane State President Chris Whaley, other college administrators, faculty and staff members were on hand at each event. Several county and city mayors, two state representatives, Roane State Foundation members and residents were among other attendees.

READ THE FULL STORY: https://www.roanestate.edu/?12420-News-Absolute-joy-at-Roane-States-drive-through-graduate-recognition-events

Each kit includes Energy Monster-themed activity sheets, a game and stickers.

Complete this form to order your free kit today: http://TVA.KidsEnergyKit.sgizmo.com/s3/

#TVAEnergyMonsters #WereAllInThisTogether

post_text:
This morning, teachers received this note from Allen Etheridge (English Teacher and ACT Coach), and it seemed all Wildcat fans should hear it, too.

Good morning, everyone. I’m emailing now from the incredible graduation setup in the Arena. I use the adjective “incredible” intentionally: I can hardly believe that we have such a graduation for our students during these challenging times. I have gotten to watch this play out from the Arena pressbox. The Graduation Committee took pains to organize a safe but celebratory graduation that will arrive on time and complete at the normal graduation time. As an ORHS graduate, former coach, and longtime teacher, I declare that this is the most Oak Ridge thing ever, and I couldn’t be more proud.

AE
Allen Etheridge
English Teacher and ACT Coach

A Message from the Board of Education to the Class of 2020:

We wish you much success in the coming years, and want to thank you for all you have accomplished. We know you have made many memories in Oak Ridge Schools that you will never forget. Let’s all step up and look ahead to what is next.

Don’t be afraid to step high, and don’t be afraid to step long. We believe in you, and know great things are ahead. Find a way to make this world a better place. We need you! Continue being a lifelong learner, learning from both successes and failures. Let us help you in your quest to be the best.

You have so much to celebrate—you have excelled, and shown how amazing you truly are. The Oak Ridge School Board celebrates you, the entire city of Oak Ridge celebrates you, and we are ALL Class of 2020 Strong!

#Classof2020Strong

https://youtu.be/wx9C-vfD9sM

post_text: Congratulations to our grant winners, and a giant thank you to Oak Ridge Public Schools Education Foundation!
shared_text:
Oak Ridge Public Schools Education Foundation
April 13 at 2:45 PM ·

We congratulate all ORS administrators, teachers, and students on the progress made with online learning last week! We would like to recognize the following educators who have been awarded over $99,000 through our 2020 Classroom Grants Program & would have been highlighted at our annual awards ceremony which was scheduled for later this month: Trudy Anderson, Heather Henderlight, Amelia Bell, Katelynn Olvey, Shayla Sanderson, Lexie Scott, Rebecca Sherlock, Stephanie Hope, Jeffrey Frendt, Lisa Meidl, Mike Carvella, Abigail Hoshall, David Tracey, Amy Fuqua, Leigh Monger, Jackie Laney, Leslie Addis, James Mitchell, Ed Wright, Jenifer Laurendine, Katy Jones, Adam Maitland, Amanda Ragan, Merny Hughey, & Patricia Wyatt. Congratulations to all! We will do our best to reschedule this event in your honor at a future date. To give to our Teacher Grants program click the yellow donate button here: https://www.orpsef.org/home
text:

post_text:
I simply love ❤️ this! Mrs. Hixson and her Linden Elementary students did such a great performance of this song “For Good,” from the musical, “Wicked.”

Here is a wonderful sampling of the words—a great message of thanks to friends.

I've heard it said
That people come into our lives for a reason
Bringing something we must learn
And we are led
To those who help us most to grow
If we let them
And we help them in return
Well, I don't know if I believe that's true
But I know I'm who I am today
Because I knew you...
I have been changed for good.

It well may be
That we will never meet again
In this lifetime
So let me say before we part
So much of me
Is made of what I learned from you
You'll be with me
Like a handprint on my heart
And now whatever way our stories end
I know you have re-written mine
By being my friend...

The Oak Ridge Schools (ORS) has been working to develop a comprehensive, unified salary schedule structure for all positions across the district. An overview of new salary schedule features for all employee groups and the proposed placement of current employees was presented at tonight’s board meeting.

The proposed salary schedules and their recommended implementation were developed to be equitable across all employee groups, aligned with current market expectations, and fiscally sustainable. They are designed to balance requirements to support ORS students, ORS current and future staff, and the sustainability of the overall school district. The school board will make decisions about the proposed salary schedules and implementation once the school district’s budgeting process is complete.

We received an awesome update from the Lego Robotics team at Jefferson Middle School (TN) we spoke to last month on Roofing Materials & Design! They won FIRST PLACE and are headed to the State Championships! WAY TO GO ATOMIC EAGLES!

Here are the kind words from their teacher:

"Thank you so much for your support of the Atomic Eagles this season. With your help, they were able to come up with an innovative project idea. They presented well at competition this past Saturday. I am proud to tell you they received the First Place Robot Design Trophy. They have earned the opportunity to compete again on February 8, 2020 at the East Tennessee State Championships.

Thanks again for your help,
Janie Shanafield "
Oak Ridge Schools
